snippet: Tina Weirather won a super-G in Germany for her first World Cup title. Weirather edged Julia Mancuso of the United States and Tina Maze, the overall World Cup winner.
abstract: Skier Tina Weirather of Liechtenstein wins super-G in Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Germany, for her first World Cup title.
lead_paragraph: Tina Weirather won a super-G in Germany for her first World Cup title. Weirather edged Julia Mancuso of the United States and Tina Maze, the overall World Cup winner.

headline.seo: Julia Mancuso and Tina Maze Edged in Super-G
headline.main: Mancuso and Maze Edged in Super-G
